Yes, Mr. Consigliere.

10
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:48,562
EPISODE 1

11
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:41,615
Why did you come here?

12
00:05:04,054 --> 00:05:06,223
GRECCO VINEYARD

13
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:22,572
How can you do business
even on the day of your boss' funeral?

14
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,337
This is the last offer from my boss,
Fabio.

15
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:40,507
An offer from his grave? Not interested.

16
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:42,300
You can take it and leave.

17
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:50,725
Killing Union President Carlo
to take over the vineyard and the union

18
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:52,894
was a mistake on your part.

19
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:55,146
He was like

20
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:58,567
a brother to Fabio.

21
00:05:58,650 --> 00:06:00,819
Whatever the offer is,
I won't be accepting it.

22
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:05,490
Does it sound like an offer to you?

23
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:12,038
This is Fabio's last act of mercy to a man

24
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,834
who killed his dear friend.

25
00:06:17,586 --> 00:06:20,338
Are you here to make a deal…

26
00:06:21,965 --> 00:06:23,008
or to threaten me?

27
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,013
If you sign this now,

28
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:30,807
there won't be any problems.

29
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:31,975
Get lost.

30
00:06:33,602 --> 00:06:36,563
Go back to your country,
you arrogant yellow.

31
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,608
I fought fair and square to take over.

32
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:41,860
The Cassano family has no shares
in this place.

33
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:43,903
Get out of here.

34
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,797
You sure you won't regret it?

35
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,511
Regret?

36
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,598
The Lucino family is backing me up.

37
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:14,643
I'm not scared to go to war.

38
00:07:18,021 --> 00:07:21,691
Regret is the most painful thing
you can experience in life.

39
00:07:23,318 --> 00:07:24,194
Emilio.

40
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:29,574
I am here to give you a chance
to redeem yourself,

41
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,243
not to start a war.

42
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:34,371
Sure. Whatever.

43
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,580
<i>Arigatou.</i>

44
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:37,749
You uncivilized yellow.

45
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:55,475
Emilio.

46
00:08:00,105 --> 00:08:01,773
You will pay

47
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:04,734
for disrespecting my people.

48
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:07,112
You neanderthal.

49
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,120
Vincenzo, did you curse at me?

50
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,163
What did you say to me?

51
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:31,219
Why are they spraying
the pesticides today?

52
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:35,682
We sprayed them last week.

53
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:42,689
Damn it! What…

54
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,736
Shit.

55
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:49,946
They're not spraying pesticides.

56
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:43,208
Oh, no! It's all burning!

57
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,959
Everything is burning!

58
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:47,378
Don't just stand there!

59
00:09:47,462 --> 00:09:50,090
Move it! Now!

60
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:52,383
Hurry!

61
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:56,304
That asshole, Vincenzo!

62
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,722
I'll get my revenge!

63
00:09:57,806 --> 00:10:00,558
I'll get back at everyone!
You and the Cassano family!

64
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,602
Hurry!

65
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:07,518
Father.

66
00:12:24,953 --> 00:12:27,497
You could have done that
after the funeral.

67
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:31,709
It was his last order.

68
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:35,004
He told me to take care of it
as soon as possible.

69
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:36,631
Even so,

70
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:40,051
burning down the entire vineyard
was stupid.

71
00:12:40,134 --> 00:12:44,847
He said I could use any means necessary
to get it done.

72
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:48,226
Right. My father always trusted
your decisions,

73
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:50,353
but never trusted mine.

74
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:56,651
Because you were always careless
when you took care of things.

75
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:01,072
You went against his word
that no matter what happens,

76
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:03,449
we do not harm women or children.

77
00:13:14,377 --> 00:13:15,378
Vincenzo.

78
00:13:16,421 --> 00:13:17,422
My friend.

79
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:19,507
My brother.

80
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:24,804
Now that I'm your boss,
I'd like to see you be more loyal.

81
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:25,888
Paolo.

82
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:27,682
My brother.

83
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:32,103
I am always ready
to show my loyalty to you…

84
00:13:36,107 --> 00:13:37,859
as long as you deserve it.

85
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:37,103
Looking for me?

86
00:16:17,185 --> 00:16:18,478
<i>Did you enjoy the party?</i>

87
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:20,271
Vincenzo.

88
00:16:22,023 --> 00:16:25,401
<i>I can hear Payan barking.
You must be heading towards the door.</i>

89
00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:29,530
How did you…

90
00:16:29,614 --> 00:16:32,408
<i>Oh, right. Let me apologize in advance.</i>

91
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:34,994
<i>I know that it's your favorite car.</i>

92
00:16:39,207 --> 00:16:43,628
<i>I didn't kill you
out of respect for Fabio.</i>

93
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:47,798
And this will be the last time.

94
00:16:52,929 --> 00:16:56,015
I'm leaving Italy
and will never come back.

95
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:00,895
Do not look for me.

96
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:13,950
The next time you try to find me,

97
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:18,162
the car will explode before you get off.

98
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:20,748
<i>Paolo.</i>

99
00:17:21,332 --> 00:17:23,417
I knew you didn't deserve to be the boss.

