GEUMGA PLAZA

103
00:18:48,294 --> 00:18:49,128
Ta-da!

104
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:52,673
Get your blood sugar up with this.

105
00:18:52,757 --> 00:18:54,008
YOU ONLY LIVE ONCE

106
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:56,719
I bought this from the most popular bakery
in Yeonnam-dong.

107
00:18:58,554 --> 00:18:59,722
I'm good. Please go.

108
00:19:01,724 --> 00:19:02,850
Eating this tasty snack

109
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:05,519
in the middle of a long day
is a form of happiness.

110
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:07,521
I'm happy enough already.

111
00:19:11,442 --> 00:19:12,485
You're happy?

112
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:14,445
Didn't you sign up as a test subject

113
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:16,781
at a pharmaceutical
to pay back your student loan?

114
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:18,658
You didn't have any side effects,

115
00:19:18,741 --> 00:19:21,410
but you were the only one
who blew the whistle.

116
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:24,246
-How can you be happy right now?
-I can.

117
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:26,248
I believe my action meant something.

118
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:28,459
You are fearless.

119
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:30,920
But…

120
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:35,758
will you still be happy
when Babel Pharmaceuticals sues you?

121
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:36,759
What?

122
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:39,804
They're livid right now.

123
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:43,182
They just ordered us
to destroy your life, Seon-ho.

124
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:51,065
No one really cares
about what happens to you.

125
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:53,901
Why? Because your sob story
won't make anyone sad.

126
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:55,319
It's not sad at all.

127
00:19:56,278 --> 00:20:00,366
I'm the only one who actually
cares about your life, Seon-ho.

128
00:20:00,449 --> 00:20:01,867
It's just me, Hong Cha-young.

129
00:20:04,995 --> 00:20:06,956
Pull the cake topper.

130
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:15,214
YOU ONLY LIVE ONCE

131
00:20:22,847 --> 00:20:24,765
How much is that?

132
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:41,657
My goodness. What a mess.

133
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,669
-Sorry, Cha-young.
-Where are you manners?

134
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:56,213
If you were late,
you should've taken a taxi.

135
00:20:56,297 --> 00:20:57,840
That's faster than a taxi.

136
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,425
Besides, that's the city's trend.

137
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:01,469
Just tell me why you're late.

138
00:21:02,303 --> 00:21:05,764
Lawyer Yoon In-seo told me
to make 1,200 copies out of the blue.

139
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:07,725
Intern Jang Joon-woo.

140
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:10,186
Tell me the kind of person
I hate the most.

141
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:11,353
Robotic people.

142
00:21:11,437 --> 00:21:13,731
Right.
People who work their ass off like robots,

143
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:16,066
but always fall short in the end.

144
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,737
I might be lacking,
but aren't I a good intern?

145
00:21:20,488 --> 00:21:21,697
A lovely intern at that?

146
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:24,158
If you start wearing different ties,

147
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:26,410
I'll think about
whether to like you or not.

148
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:29,371
But Steve Jobs wore the same turtlenecks.

149
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:31,624
I prefer sophisticated men
to stubborn men.

150
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:37,963
COURTHOUSE

151
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:40,674
DAY 1 OF THE HEARING
FOR BABEL PHARMCEAUTICAL'S LAWSUIT

152
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:03,364
Claiming the victims died
from the side effects of the drug

153
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:04,782
is still preposterous.

154
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:07,576
The plaintiff is provoking the press
with unproven evidence.

155
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:10,663
The victims all passed away
from cardiac infarction

156
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:11,747
and had no prior conditions.

157
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:14,583
One of them had arrhythmia.
Another had pulmonary edema.

158
00:22:14,667 --> 00:22:16,627
And another had low blood pressure.

159
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:20,673
She extracted these conditions
from the victims' old medical histories.

160
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:22,174
The paramedics on the scene

161
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:24,885
stated that they showed typical signs
of an overdose.

162
00:22:24,969 --> 00:22:27,096
Paramedics aren't licensed doctors.

163
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:29,890
They only stated the external symptoms.

164
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:33,894
Your Honor, I have the recording-based
statement from one of the test subjects.

165
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:37,773
Babel coerced him
to make a false statement

166
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:39,191
to silence the others.

167
00:22:39,275 --> 00:22:41,777
-This statement clearly states--
-Your Honor.

168
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:44,280
The test subject who made the statement

169
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,865
turned himself in for perjury an hour ago.

170
00:22:47,908 --> 00:22:50,035
I submit the interrogation report
as evidence.

171
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:55,708
After perjuring himself,
the witness planned

172
00:22:55,791 --> 00:22:58,961
to extort money from Babel Pharm
through the plaintiff's counsel.

173
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:00,879
But as he was conscience-stricken,

174
00:23:00,963 --> 00:23:03,507
-he decided to turn himself in.
-Your Honor.

175
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:08,304
It's a one-sided statement. His perjury
charge hasn't been established.

176
00:23:08,387 --> 00:23:10,389
The recording should
be admissible in court.

177
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:13,475
We will rule
once the witness' perjury charge

178
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:14,727
has been established.

179
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:18,564
The next hearing will be held
a week from today in this courtroom.

180
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,736
That is all.

181
00:23:32,578 --> 00:23:33,704
Give me a cigarette.

182
00:23:34,705 --> 00:23:36,707
-I quit two years ago.
-Just leave, then.

183
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:41,211
At least wash your hair
when you come to court.

184
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:45,633
I don't need that from you. Just go.

185
00:23:47,676 --> 00:23:49,678
We could have just settled out of court.

186
00:23:49,762 --> 00:23:53,432
How could you start this mess
when you weren't even sure you could win?

187
00:23:54,767 --> 00:23:55,726
Start this mess?

188
00:23:57,561 --> 00:24:00,522
-That's no way to talk to your father.
-I thought you disowned me.

189
00:24:01,357 --> 00:24:02,483
Right.

190
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:05,486
No daughter of mine would
buy off a witness like that.

191
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:07,946
Do you find peace
when you criticize your daughter?

192
00:24:08,030 --> 00:24:09,740
You and Babel deserve it.

193
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:11,241
You guys are like mafias.

194
00:24:13,327 --> 00:24:16,580
How could you be so proud
of destroying the powerless?

195
00:24:20,751 --> 00:24:21,585
Dad.

196
00:24:22,503 --> 00:24:24,213
Can't you stop?

197
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:27,633
Even if you don't treat me
like your daughter,

198
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:31,178
I still worry so much about you.

199
00:24:31,261 --> 00:24:33,764
I worry that this might be
taking a toll on you

200
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:35,683
physically and emotionally.

201
00:24:37,142 --> 00:24:38,268
Dad.

202
00:24:38,352 --> 00:24:42,690
If you stop, I'll help you.

203
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:47,194
I'm embarrassed to say this now,
but now that I'm older,

204
00:24:48,237 --> 00:24:50,197
I realized that family comes first.

205
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:58,330
-Cha-young.
-Yes, Dad.

206
00:24:58,414 --> 00:25:01,875
Why don't you quit being a lawyer
and start anew as an actor?

207
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:05,337
That way, you won't ruin
other people's lives.

208
00:25:09,049 --> 00:25:10,592
You'll never beat me!

209
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:13,971
We'll find out when it ends.

210
00:25:14,054 --> 00:25:17,099
Also, I've made up my mind.
I am really going to disown you.

211
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:18,350
How will you do that?

212
00:25:19,268 --> 00:25:20,602
I'm sure I'll find a way.

213
00:25:21,478 --> 00:25:22,438
Bye.

214
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:36,785
Excuse me.

215
00:25:37,828 --> 00:25:39,204
I need to do an inspection.

216
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:44,376
WANTED
NAME: PARK JEONG-GUK

217
00:25:45,127 --> 00:25:47,045
May I see your identification?

218
00:25:54,052 --> 00:25:55,679
REPUBLICA ITALIANA
VINCENZO CASSANO

219
00:26:00,851 --> 00:26:03,520
Gosh. You're Korean Italian.

220
00:26:03,604 --> 00:26:05,856
I'm so sorry. Gosh, my bad.

221
00:26:06,690 --> 00:26:09,777
The wanted man is Korean, you see.

222
00:26:11,236 --> 00:26:12,196
Gosh, I'm sorry.

223
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:16,700
Oh, my. You have such a cool name.

224
00:26:16,784 --> 00:26:18,786
"Vincen Zo"?

225
00:26:18,869 --> 00:26:20,871
Which Zo clan are you from?

226
00:26:28,462 --> 00:26:31,048
-Give me back my passport.
-Okay.

227
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:38,889
Yes. Mr. Cho. I got here safely.

228
00:26:40,516 --> 00:26:41,600
I see.

229
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:43,936
See you there, then.

230
00:26:44,728 --> 00:26:46,855
It will take about an hour and a half.

231
00:26:47,564 --> 00:26:48,524
Okay.

232
00:26:49,483 --> 00:26:52,194
Come on. How can they cancel
when I just got here?

233
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:56,865
Excuse me. Are you looking for a taxi?

234
00:26:57,658 --> 00:26:58,700
Yes.

235
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:01,829
I drive a limousine.

236
00:27:01,912 --> 00:27:04,456
My appointment just got canceled,
so I am available.

237
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:05,582
Where are you headed?

238
00:27:07,251 --> 00:27:08,544
Geumga-dong, Seoul.

239
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:11,922
Really? Then, I promise to
give you a comfortable ride.

240
00:27:12,005 --> 00:27:13,507
-I'm good.
-I'm good, too.

241
00:27:13,590 --> 00:27:15,467
Please get in. All right.

242
00:27:17,678 --> 00:27:19,346
Gosh, you're so handsome.

243
00:27:37,114 --> 00:27:39,283
Did you enjoy your trip?

244
00:27:40,367 --> 00:27:41,827
Where did you go?

245
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:43,704
I'd prefer not to talk.

246
00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:45,539
Okay. I apologize.

247
00:27:51,503 --> 00:27:52,671
Turn on the news instead.

248
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:54,214
Okay.

249
00:27:56,592 --> 00:27:58,427
<i>…was apprehended by the police.</i>

250
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,888
<i>In several fishing villages,
Korea Coast Guard…</i>

251
00:28:00,971 --> 00:28:03,098
<i>I must finish everything in a month.</i>

252
00:28:04,057 --> 00:28:06,226
<i>Then I'll leave for Malta right away.</i>

253
00:28:06,310 --> 00:28:10,606
<i>There have been many reports of crimes
against foreigners at our airport.</i>

254
00:28:10,689 --> 00:28:13,942
<i>According to the police, they pretend
to be taxi drivers at the airport,</i>

255
00:28:14,026 --> 00:28:16,445
<i>offer drinks after spiking them
with sleeping pills,</i>

256
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:19,948
<i>-and steal their valuables. Especially…</i>
-Gosh, these assholes.

257
00:28:20,032 --> 00:28:24,077
How could they when Bong Joon-ho
and BTS worked so hard for our image?

