270
00:29:06,662 --> 00:29:07,621
Can they reattach it?

271
00:29:08,205 --> 00:29:09,206
Damn it.

272
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:14,252
Ma'am, ten minutes ago, Masato of
the Kawaguchi Gang stabbed himself

273
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:17,547
with a bread knife at a bakery in Busan
when our agents surrounded him.

274
00:29:17,631 --> 00:29:19,258
What? With a bread knife?

275
00:29:19,341 --> 00:29:21,301
Gosh, that's really long.

276
00:29:21,885 --> 00:29:23,637
-Call for a helicopter and move out.
-Okay.

277
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:27,099
So what? Do you have the details?

278
00:29:27,182 --> 00:29:28,767
How the hell did he get here?

279
00:29:50,706 --> 00:29:51,581
He's…

280
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:54,251
He's a consigliere to the mafia.

281
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:56,336
He's in Korea?

282
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:05,053
When he came to Korea five years ago,
he was just an ordinary lawyer.

283
00:30:05,137 --> 00:30:08,682
But now, he's no longer a small fry.
He's the key member of the mafia.

284
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:11,893
He came back to Korea as a consigliere.

285
00:30:16,023 --> 00:30:17,274
Hey, Mr. An.

286
00:30:17,858 --> 00:30:21,987
Why would they come all the way to Korea?
To achieve what?

287
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:23,989
There's a lot here in Korea.

288
00:30:24,072 --> 00:30:25,907
We're a global target now.

289
00:30:25,991 --> 00:30:28,452
Then, perhaps,
he just came here on a holiday

290
00:30:28,535 --> 00:30:30,829
to have bulgogi, <i>dongdongju,
makgeolli</i>, and <i>pajeon</i>.

291
00:30:30,912 --> 00:30:32,205
We should welcome him.

292
00:30:32,289 --> 00:30:35,083
Sir, this isn't something
you should take lightly.

293
00:30:35,167 --> 00:30:37,627
-The consigliere is a mafia's--
-What about it?

294
00:30:38,462 --> 00:30:40,881
What the heck is that supposed to be?

295
00:30:40,964 --> 00:30:43,216
It's like you're trying to get scolded.

296
00:30:43,300 --> 00:30:44,926
We have to track him, sir!

297
00:30:45,761 --> 00:30:48,138
The Italian mafia are a heinous bunch.

298
00:30:48,221 --> 00:30:49,806
Just let him be.

299
00:30:49,890 --> 00:30:52,100
Don't you dare launch some operation.

300
00:30:52,184 --> 00:30:53,852
-But he's the consigliere--
-Why you…

301
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:15,165
Ms. Hong, I heard
you scored a big one today.

302
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:16,917
Congratulations, Ms. Hong.

303
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,960
You are indeed my role model.

304
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:35,352
<i>Yes, I did it again today</i>

305
00:31:35,435 --> 00:31:37,020
<i>Go, Hong Cha-young</i>

306
00:31:37,104 --> 00:31:38,772
<i>You're so cool, Cha-young</i>

307
00:31:38,855 --> 00:31:41,900
<i>I am so cool</i>

308
00:31:41,983 --> 00:31:43,360
<i>Yes, yes, yes</i>

309
00:31:45,946 --> 00:31:50,075
<i>Hong Cha-young, Hong Cha,
Hong Cha, Hong Cha-young</i>

310
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:53,870
I should install blinds here.

311
00:31:53,954 --> 00:31:55,205
Everyone can see through.

312
00:31:57,457 --> 00:32:00,961
Come on, you should've gone easy on him.
He's your dad.

313
00:32:02,462 --> 00:32:05,173
He's not my dad.
He's the counsel for the plaintiff.

314
00:32:07,259 --> 00:32:10,053
Your dad still goes by his nickname
the Tosa among the alumni.

315
00:32:10,137 --> 00:32:13,181
That's why he always takes things too far,
not knowing when to stop.

316
00:32:13,849 --> 00:32:15,434
I'll end this at the next hearing.

317
00:32:15,517 --> 00:32:16,852
Yes. That's it.

318
00:32:17,519 --> 00:32:21,773
A competent lawyer can end things
before things get out of hand.

319
00:32:25,527 --> 00:32:28,738
I should've quashed this
when he filed the petition. I'm sorry.

320
00:32:28,822 --> 00:32:29,781
It's okay.

321
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:35,537
You should get off work early today
and have some fun.

322
00:32:35,620 --> 00:32:36,746
Oh, right.

323
00:32:37,914 --> 00:32:39,541
Check your bank account.

324
00:32:41,293 --> 00:32:42,210
It's a bonus.

325
00:32:45,547 --> 00:32:47,299
You don't have to give me a bonus.

326
00:32:48,383 --> 00:32:50,927
You are already treating me so well here.

327
00:32:53,013 --> 00:32:54,139
Hold on.

328
00:32:55,390 --> 00:32:57,392
Gosh, I'm so touched.

329
00:32:58,643 --> 00:33:02,480
It's fine. Just take it
and spend it all today.

330
00:33:02,564 --> 00:33:04,441
Gosh, Cha-young.

331
00:33:05,192 --> 00:33:06,902
<i>Cha-young, Cha-young, Hong Cha-young</i>

332
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:08,904
I'm so moved. I'm serious.

333
00:33:12,782 --> 00:33:14,534
Did he deduct taxes again?

334
00:33:16,036 --> 00:33:17,120
Come on.

335
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,416
His meals must've been salty.

336
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:24,336
I didn't even ask him to drink it.
He just drank it on his own.

337
00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:26,630
Hey, didn't I tell you?

338
00:33:27,255 --> 00:33:29,591
When I saw him at the airport,
I knew he was loaded.

339
00:33:29,674 --> 00:33:31,510
Gosh, this is a designer bag, too.

340
00:33:31,593 --> 00:33:32,719
Wait. What's this?

341
00:33:36,139 --> 00:33:37,641
This must be over 4,000 dollars.

342
00:33:41,436 --> 00:33:43,146
-Holy shit.
-Hey.

343
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:44,439
Look at his watch.

344
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:48,443
If this is authentic,
it'll cost over 100 million won.

345
00:33:48,526 --> 00:33:50,153
Hey. It can't be a knockoff, right?

346
00:33:52,906 --> 00:33:55,075
-Gosh, no way.
-Right? Right.

347
00:33:55,158 --> 00:33:56,201
Look at his style.

348
00:33:56,284 --> 00:33:58,745
He'd never wear a fake watch.

349
00:33:58,828 --> 00:34:00,038
-Hey.
-Look at this.

350
00:34:00,121 --> 00:34:01,873
-He even smells good, too.
-Really?

351
00:34:02,582 --> 00:34:03,959
Find his cologne, too.

352
00:34:06,253 --> 00:34:07,170
You're up.

353
00:34:10,131 --> 00:34:11,716
Who are you guys?

354
00:34:12,342 --> 00:34:13,426
Us?

355
00:34:14,177 --> 00:34:15,554
We are what you think we are.

356
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:18,682
Seriously?

357
00:34:19,307 --> 00:34:20,684
Gosh, that sounded so cool.

358
00:34:21,309 --> 00:34:23,395
-I told you you were talented.
-Drop the beat.

359
00:34:41,788 --> 00:34:43,206
50,000 WON

360
00:35:04,978 --> 00:35:07,772
I swear I'm going to catch
you assholes and kill you!

361
00:35:07,856 --> 00:35:09,149
I swear to God I will!

362
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:12,819
Stupid Korea.

363
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:15,822
Stupid Korea!

364
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:17,866
Be quiet!

365
00:35:17,949 --> 00:35:19,743
I told you to be quiet!

366
00:35:20,327 --> 00:35:21,494
Shit.

367
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:24,664
Damn it.

368
00:35:25,999 --> 00:35:27,000
Shut up!

369
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:39,346
Damn it.

370
00:35:41,806 --> 00:35:44,142
Damn it!

371
00:35:44,225 --> 00:35:47,103
50,000 WON

372
00:35:56,279 --> 00:36:01,076
Damn Korea! Damn it! Damn you, Korea!

373
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:03,036
You're dead!

374
00:36:03,787 --> 00:36:05,246
Damn it!

375
00:36:08,500 --> 00:36:10,668
Damn it!

376
00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:13,213
Look over there.

377
00:36:13,296 --> 00:36:16,299
He seems like a nice person
now that I get a closer look.

378
00:36:16,383 --> 00:36:18,134
-He's so handsome.
-He is.

379
00:36:18,218 --> 00:36:19,678
-He seems nice.
-Yes.

380
00:36:19,761 --> 00:36:21,638
She only likes handsome guys.

381
00:36:21,721 --> 00:36:23,473
-Seriously.
-Gosh.

382
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:27,686
Here.

383
00:36:27,769 --> 00:36:29,979
Like this. Go ahead.

384
00:36:34,317 --> 00:36:36,361
-It looks like he was beat up.
-Really?

385
00:36:36,444 --> 00:36:39,906
-He's sure is handsome.
-That's all you care about.

386
00:37:03,847 --> 00:37:07,809
GEUMGA PLAZA

387
00:37:11,146 --> 00:37:13,857
CONGRATULATIONS ON PASSING
THE ARCHITECTURAL REVIEW

388
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:16,776
<i>My goal is</i>

389
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:20,947
<i>tearing down this building.</i>

390
00:37:21,698 --> 00:37:23,366
What do you need advice with?

391
00:37:23,450 --> 00:37:25,410
5 YEARS AGO, MILAN
CASSANO FAMILY'S STUDY

392
00:37:25,493 --> 00:37:28,163
My friend, Fabio, told me

393
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:32,667
that you knew a safe way to hide my gold.

394
00:37:33,710 --> 00:37:35,670
He said his old friend, Fabio, told him

395
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:39,924
that you would tell him
how to safely hide his gold.

396
00:37:40,008 --> 00:37:43,762
I want to hide my gold in Korea,
not China.

397
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:50,018
And it must be kept safe to the point
that no one can steal it.

398
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:52,479
He wants to hide it in Korea.

399
00:37:52,562 --> 00:37:55,815
And he wants it to be safe to the point
that no one can steal it.

400
00:37:58,985 --> 00:38:02,947
<i>There is this method our family uses
which has been passed down for 50 years.</i>

401
00:38:03,656 --> 00:38:05,867
<i>Buy an old building in Korea.</i>

402
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:08,036
<i>Buy the building under my friend,</i>

403
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:11,414
<i>Mr. Cho's name
so you don't raise any suspicions.</i>

404
00:38:11,498 --> 00:38:16,169
<i>And then, make one of the lots
look like either a shop or a company.</i>

405
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:17,086
UNDER CONSTRUCTION

406
00:38:19,798 --> 00:38:21,549
<i>And hire technicians</i>

407
00:38:21,633 --> 00:38:24,511
<i>to create a secret room in the basement
to store your gold.</i>

408
00:38:28,932 --> 00:38:33,269
<i>To avoid getting caught,
transport the gold little by little.</i>

409
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:37,649
<i>To open the secret room,</i>

410
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:41,486
<i>the biometric system that recognizes
only you should be utilized.</i>

411
00:38:42,612 --> 00:38:45,907
<i>It must only recognize you.
Not even your family or friends.</i>

412
00:38:59,963 --> 00:39:01,381
<i>But there's more.</i>

413
00:39:02,048 --> 00:39:03,550
<i>That secret room</i>

414
00:39:04,551 --> 00:39:06,761
<i>comes with a special feature.</i>

415
00:39:06,844 --> 00:39:08,096
Sir.

416
00:39:08,805 --> 00:39:11,224
-Mr. Cho, have you been well?
-Yes.

417
00:39:12,433 --> 00:39:15,562
What on earth happened to you?

418
00:39:16,896 --> 00:39:18,106
It's nothing.

419
00:39:21,234 --> 00:39:22,527
What about my residence?

420
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:24,862
I heard you were coming,
so I had it cleaned.

421
00:39:24,946 --> 00:39:27,532
And I also put away your items
and clothes from Italy.

422
00:39:27,615 --> 00:39:29,784
-Let's get going now.
-Okay.

423
00:39:31,411 --> 00:39:33,121
How are things going?

424
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:34,622
As you read it in the file,

425
00:39:34,706 --> 00:39:37,125
the Development Opposition Committee
has been formed.

426
00:39:37,208 --> 00:39:39,836
I already told them that
I wouldn't sell off the building.

427
00:39:39,919 --> 00:39:41,212
But they won't believe me.

428
00:39:41,296 --> 00:39:42,338
Oh, right.

429
00:39:42,422 --> 00:39:45,550
Babel E&C bought
all the shops around the plaza.

430
00:39:46,759 --> 00:39:49,304
Any other pressure from Babel E&C?

431
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:51,723
Nothing, other than the team leader
of Investment and Development

432
00:39:51,806 --> 00:39:53,600
coming here daily to make an offer.

433
00:40:20,877 --> 00:40:21,878
Sir.

434
00:40:28,384 --> 00:40:29,385
The bathroom…

435
00:40:30,136 --> 00:40:31,304
Damn it.

436
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:54,827
I already set up the bed
and blankets for you.

437
00:40:54,911 --> 00:40:58,539
And I will schedule a meeting
with the tenants tomorrow.

438
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:01,960
Okay. Sure.

439
00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:06,673
Once this project is done,

440
00:41:06,756 --> 00:41:09,300
are you interested in staying in Korea?

441
00:41:13,513 --> 00:41:14,430
No.

442
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:16,474
I see.

443
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:21,104
I put your new cell phone, cash,
and the things you asked for

444
00:41:21,187 --> 00:41:22,689
in the bedroom.

445
00:41:23,356 --> 00:41:24,357
Okay.

446
00:41:28,277 --> 00:41:29,153
What's that?

447
00:41:30,071 --> 00:41:33,449
Oh, the previous tenants put them up.

448
00:41:35,243 --> 00:41:36,327
Should I get them off?

449
00:41:37,620 --> 00:41:39,414
That's fine. I won't be here long.

450
00:41:43,376 --> 00:41:44,919
Gosh, that's a lot.

451
00:41:46,087 --> 00:41:47,463
<i>-Really?
-Yes.</i>

452
00:41:47,547 --> 00:41:48,464
JIPURAGI LAW FIRM

453
00:41:48,548 --> 00:41:53,094
I definitely saw a man with
the building owner at the entrance.

454
00:41:53,594 --> 00:41:54,512
So I followed them.

455
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:59,100
