836
01:10:50,079 --> 01:10:51,038
I'm not interested.

837
01:10:55,293 --> 01:10:56,586
I'm so sick of him.

838
01:11:05,303 --> 01:11:06,846
GEUMGA PLAZA CONTRACT OF SALES

839
01:11:06,929 --> 01:11:08,848
Don't you think I'd be a better actor?

840
01:11:09,724 --> 01:11:11,517
Of course, sir.

841
01:11:11,601 --> 01:11:13,811
-Gosh, that's a no-brainer.
-Come over here.

842
01:11:17,815 --> 01:11:19,233
Yes.

843
01:11:20,067 --> 01:11:21,277
Okay. I got it.

844
01:11:23,946 --> 01:11:26,157
Check your bank account. It's over.

845
01:11:27,116 --> 01:11:28,451
Hey, let's go.

846
01:11:28,534 --> 01:11:29,577
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

847
01:11:29,660 --> 01:11:30,870
Gosh, let's go.

848
01:11:38,461 --> 01:11:41,506
It says that by nature of clinical trials…

849
01:11:41,589 --> 01:11:42,840
Hello, Ms. Hong.

850
01:11:44,342 --> 01:11:47,553
Who are you to barge into my office?
That's some nasty manner you have.

851
01:11:48,387 --> 01:11:49,806
What's this?

852
01:11:50,348 --> 01:11:51,265
Oh, that?

853
01:11:52,058 --> 01:11:54,519
I mailed that to remove you
from my family registry.

854
01:11:56,479 --> 01:11:58,105
You can't do that anymore.

855
01:11:58,189 --> 01:12:00,691
The family registration system
was abolished ages ago.

856
01:12:00,775 --> 01:12:01,818
You're a lawyer.

857
01:12:01,901 --> 01:12:04,695
I can still try, can't I?

858
01:12:04,779 --> 01:12:06,197
-Hey.
-Yes.

859
01:12:06,280 --> 01:12:07,281
This one, too.

860
01:12:07,365 --> 01:12:10,660
And look at this. This is ridiculous.

861
01:12:10,743 --> 01:12:13,371
"The petitioner rejects
the following words

862
01:12:13,454 --> 01:12:16,666
and any similar words from the recipient.
The following words are,

863
01:12:16,749 --> 01:12:19,919
<i>appa, abuji,</i> papa, daddy,
<i>otosang, bàba,</i> and <i>père</i>."

864
01:12:20,670 --> 01:12:22,588
This is just outright ridiculous.

865
01:12:23,881 --> 01:12:25,550
It's so immature.

866
01:12:28,678 --> 01:12:29,929
-Mr. Nam.
-Yes?

867
01:12:30,012 --> 01:12:31,639
I'm talking here.

868
01:12:31,722 --> 01:12:33,266
Go ahead.

869
01:12:33,349 --> 01:12:34,475
LAUNDRY MASTER TAK HONG-SIK

870
01:12:35,643 --> 01:12:38,854
Damn it. How is this even possible?

871
01:12:39,564 --> 01:12:43,025
You Korean. Damn you. Get out of my sight!

872
01:12:43,109 --> 01:12:44,527
Damn it.

873
01:12:45,403 --> 01:12:46,571
Yes.

874
01:12:47,154 --> 01:12:49,073
What happened to my suit?

875
01:12:49,156 --> 01:12:51,742
It's because your suit
was made from cheap fabric.

876
01:12:51,826 --> 01:12:54,412
-It doesn't happen to good fabric.
-Cheap?

877
01:12:54,495 --> 01:12:56,372
-Do you know how much this is?
-How much?

878
01:12:56,455 --> 01:12:58,749
This is a limited edition
from Booralro's line…

879
01:13:00,918 --> 01:13:02,795
There's no point in talking to him.

880
01:13:04,922 --> 01:13:07,758
By the way, you have a nice build.

881
01:13:07,842 --> 01:13:10,636
You know? You still look cool
with that tight suit.

882
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:11,971
This might catch on.

883
01:13:12,054 --> 01:13:14,682
Did you do this on purpose?

884
01:13:14,765 --> 01:13:17,894
What are you talking about?
I'm the laundry master.

885
01:13:17,977 --> 01:13:19,812
Then you shouldn't have messed up!

886
01:13:24,775 --> 01:13:26,277
You will have to pay

887
01:13:27,236 --> 01:13:29,280
for what you did to my suit.

888
01:13:29,363 --> 01:13:30,615
You will.

889
01:13:35,202 --> 01:13:39,707
<i>Tenants of Geumga Plaza,
come out of the building now.</i>

890
01:13:39,790 --> 01:13:41,959
Someone's looking for me.
Pay before you go.

891
01:13:44,420 --> 01:13:45,796
Damn it.

892
01:13:51,802 --> 01:13:52,887
Yes, Mr. Cho.

893
01:13:53,512 --> 01:13:56,098
My wife and daughter were
taken hostage. I had no choice.

894
01:13:57,475 --> 01:13:58,517
I'm sorry.

895
01:13:59,310 --> 01:14:01,687
I'll fix this no matter what.

896
01:14:02,396 --> 01:14:03,606
Yes. I will…

897
01:14:09,070 --> 01:14:10,071
Mr. Cho.

898
01:14:11,280 --> 01:14:14,659
Mr. Cho. Mr. Cho? Mr. Cho!

899
01:14:14,742 --> 01:14:18,954
Fine. I can overlook everything
you wrote here. I can live with that.

900
01:14:19,455 --> 01:14:21,207
But this one. Look.

901
01:14:21,958 --> 01:14:25,670
"All the photos that the recipient
took with the petitioner as a minor and

902
01:14:25,753 --> 01:14:28,673
photos that remind the recipient
of the petitioner as the parent

903
01:14:28,756 --> 01:14:31,842
will be donated for the exhibition,
Geumga-dong's History,

904
01:14:31,926 --> 01:14:34,553
held at the Sangcheon District Office
for public interest."

905
01:14:35,179 --> 01:14:37,348
Who are you to donate my photos?

906
01:14:37,431 --> 01:14:39,809
They're the epitome
of my embarrassing past!

907
01:14:39,892 --> 01:14:41,102
It's up to me.

908
01:14:41,185 --> 01:14:42,770
I raised you.

909
01:14:42,853 --> 01:14:46,273
And does that give you the right
to abandon me? This is embarrassing!

910
01:14:46,357 --> 01:14:47,566
"Embarrassing"?

911
01:14:48,150 --> 01:14:50,403
It's because what you do
is less than human!

912
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:56,033
You're a lawyer. How could you not
have a sense of duty or justice?

913
01:14:56,117 --> 01:15:00,079
Your sense of duty just makes you
the nosiest lawyer in the world!

914
01:15:00,162 --> 01:15:04,250
And your sense of justice is just
groundless hostility against the rich!

915
01:15:04,333 --> 01:15:06,711
This is called mechanical justice!

916
01:15:06,794 --> 01:15:07,878
"Mechanical justice"?

917
01:15:07,962 --> 01:15:09,964
Then is following money
"rational justice"?

918
01:15:10,047 --> 01:15:13,092
Yes. Money is justice in Korea.

919
01:15:13,175 --> 01:15:14,468
And power means justice.

920
01:15:14,552 --> 01:15:16,303
Then, keep living your life like that!

921
01:15:16,804 --> 01:15:19,473
But do not show your face around me. Okay?

922
01:15:19,557 --> 01:15:22,309
Okay. Let's cut off all ties!

923
01:15:22,393 --> 01:15:23,894
-Yes. Let's do that.
-Don't.

924
01:15:23,978 --> 01:15:25,604
Let's never call each other.

925
01:15:25,688 --> 01:15:27,523
-I won't.
-Don't you dare call me!

926
01:15:27,606 --> 01:15:28,649
-I won't.
-Mr. Hong!

927
01:15:28,733 --> 01:15:29,692
Never call me!

928
01:15:29,775 --> 01:15:30,901
Mr. Hong.

929
01:15:32,611 --> 01:15:35,698
You have to come outside now.

930
01:15:36,532 --> 01:15:39,452
GEUMGA PLAZA

931
01:15:42,580 --> 01:15:43,664
Hello.

932
01:15:44,915 --> 01:15:47,501
My gosh. You're a bunch of lazy bums.

933
01:15:48,335 --> 01:15:50,212
Why haven't you put up the signs?

934
01:15:51,088 --> 01:15:52,173
Do it now.

935
01:15:53,215 --> 01:15:54,341
Aren't you cold?

936
01:15:55,509 --> 01:15:56,635
Let's go.

937
01:15:56,719 --> 01:15:57,970
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

938
01:16:02,141 --> 01:16:03,267
NOTICE

939
01:16:03,350 --> 01:16:04,894
SELLER: CHO YEONG-UN,
BUYER: BABEL E&C

940
01:16:04,977 --> 01:16:06,228
-What happened?
-What?

941
01:16:06,312 --> 01:16:07,980
-But he promised.
-What happened?

942
01:16:08,064 --> 01:16:09,273
What do we do, then?

943
01:16:09,356 --> 01:16:10,858
-Put it up. Just do it.
-Okay.

944
01:16:10,941 --> 01:16:12,276
Cover up the sign.

945
01:16:13,819 --> 01:16:15,196
Hello, sir.

946
01:16:20,284 --> 01:16:21,702
Nice to meet you.

947
01:16:21,786 --> 01:16:23,370
I'm Park Seok-do, the CEO of Ant Company

948
01:16:23,454 --> 01:16:26,874
and the chairman of the Development
Committee for Babel Tower.

949
01:16:30,211 --> 01:16:31,545
What kind of company is that?

950
01:16:31,629 --> 01:16:33,714
It's a shady company
that performs dirty jobs

951
01:16:33,798 --> 01:16:36,300
like high interest loans
and beating people up.

952
01:16:36,383 --> 01:16:37,343
I see.

953
01:16:37,426 --> 01:16:41,096
Oh, right. As of today,
this building belongs to Babel E&C.

954
01:16:41,180 --> 01:16:44,517
Starting today,
the Compensation Team will visit you.

955
01:16:44,600 --> 01:16:47,102
Let's handle this peacefully.

956
01:16:47,186 --> 01:16:49,313
I knew it. Damn it.

957
01:16:49,396 --> 01:16:52,024
This was their plan. But what?
They'll let us move back in?

958
01:16:52,108 --> 01:16:55,444
That lousy Vincenzo or whatever.
I should've shrunk his suit even more.

959
01:16:55,528 --> 01:16:56,779
-Where is he?
-Right.

960
01:16:56,862 --> 01:17:00,366
If any of the tenants give us a hard time,

961
01:17:00,449 --> 01:17:05,746
one of these uncompromising men
will tire you out physically and mentally.

962
01:17:05,830 --> 01:17:06,789
Hey.

963
01:17:06,872 --> 01:17:08,916
Are you crazy? What are you doing?

964
01:17:08,999 --> 01:17:10,501
-Why?
-Who are you?

965
01:17:14,839 --> 01:17:17,258
-You can't do this.
-Why not?

966
01:17:19,885 --> 01:17:21,929
-Are you okay?
-You startled me.

967
01:17:22,012 --> 01:17:22,930
I thought I hit you.

968
01:17:27,393 --> 01:17:29,895
You can't block the path to the restroom.

969
01:17:30,729 --> 01:17:34,066
-What about the people who need to go?
-You got me excited for a second.

970
01:17:34,733 --> 01:17:35,901
Goodness.

971
01:17:36,569 --> 01:17:38,529
-Guys, step aside. Gosh. It's urgent.
-Okay.

972
01:17:38,612 --> 01:17:40,990
I don't want him to do his business here.
Hurry.

973
01:17:41,073 --> 01:17:43,450
-Go. Go ahead.
-Thank you.

974
01:17:44,910 --> 01:17:48,080
My goodness, that idiot.
He's so embarrassing.

975
01:17:48,164 --> 01:17:49,373
Leave now.

976
01:17:49,456 --> 01:17:53,043
You're violating the law
by threatening us like this.

977
01:17:53,127 --> 01:17:56,505
Why don't you stop already?
We will compensate you handsomely.

978
01:17:56,589 --> 01:17:58,215
You say you'll compensate us,

979
01:17:58,299 --> 01:18:00,426
but you'll just beat us up
and kick us out.

980
01:18:00,509 --> 01:18:04,054
This is a good occasion.
Why are you ruining the mood?

981
01:18:04,138 --> 01:18:05,431
-Gosh.
-Hey.

982
01:18:07,892 --> 01:18:08,767
Who are you?

983
01:18:08,851 --> 01:18:11,312
I'm his only daughter.

984
01:18:11,395 --> 01:18:14,106
And I'm Lawyer Hong Cha-young
of Law Firm Wusang.

985
01:18:14,940 --> 01:18:17,735
-You're not my daughter.
-Come on. Be quiet.

986
01:18:20,279 --> 01:18:23,532
-What is a lawyer from Wusang doing here?
-It's none of your business.

987
01:18:24,700 --> 01:18:27,286
This isn't the way
to go about your business.

988
01:18:27,369 --> 01:18:29,914
Don't you know the era we live in?

989
01:18:29,997 --> 01:18:32,249
It's not like we're in
some '90s gangster movie!

990
01:18:32,333 --> 01:18:33,500
Hey, miss.

991
01:18:33,584 --> 01:18:37,171
Do you want to get beaten up
like the movies from the '90s?

992
01:18:38,172 --> 01:18:40,299
-My goodness.
-Hey!

993
01:18:46,639 --> 01:18:48,933
If you touch me again,

994
01:18:49,558 --> 01:18:51,810
I'll make you pay for what you did!

995
01:18:51,894 --> 01:18:55,189
Sure. Okay. Let's see how much money
I have to pay to settle with you!

996
01:18:55,272 --> 01:18:57,399
Stop!

997
01:19:25,219 --> 01:19:26,387
What did he say?

998
01:19:29,139 --> 01:19:30,933
Where's my tape measure?

999
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,315
Do you also need to use the bathroom?

1000
01:19:39,149 --> 01:19:40,401
Is it urgent?

1001
01:19:40,484 --> 01:19:42,027
Go ahead. Go on.

1002
01:19:42,111 --> 01:19:43,821
-Go.
-Let's talk.

1003
01:19:44,321 --> 01:19:45,698
Who the heck are you?

1004
01:19:45,781 --> 01:19:48,117
Vincenzo Cassano.

1005
01:19:48,784 --> 01:19:52,413
I represent the owner of Geumga Plaza,
Cho Yeong-un.

1006
01:19:52,496 --> 01:19:54,331
"Vinchenzo Quassano"?

1007
01:19:54,415 --> 01:19:55,708
This is ridiculous.

1008
01:19:55,791 --> 01:19:58,335
There's no talking your way out of this.

1009
01:20:03,924 --> 01:20:05,300
Hey, hold on.

1010
01:20:09,013 --> 01:20:10,097
Goodness.

1011
01:20:11,348 --> 01:20:13,851
I'm not that curious, but I'll listen.

1012
01:20:19,898 --> 01:20:21,150
So what is it?

1013
01:20:26,780 --> 01:20:27,781
-Sir!
-Sir!

1014
01:20:31,452 --> 01:20:33,787
-My nose is bleeding!
-A nosebleed?

1015
01:20:33,871 --> 01:20:36,498
Gosh. Come on. Seriously.

1016
01:20:37,207 --> 01:20:38,542
You jerk.

1017
01:20:43,338 --> 01:20:45,340
-Oh, no!
-Boss!

1018
01:20:45,424 --> 01:20:47,259
If you take one more step…

1019
01:20:50,721 --> 01:20:53,265
-your boss will fall.
-Don't move, you dimwits.

1020
01:20:53,348 --> 01:20:54,641
Just stay still.

1021
01:20:54,725 --> 01:20:56,602
Everyone, stay still.

1022
01:21:01,815 --> 01:21:04,109
Given the height of the building,
you won't die.

1023
01:21:04,193 --> 01:21:05,694
You'll just break your leg.

1024
01:21:08,697 --> 01:21:11,408
But if you're unlucky and fall head-first,

1025
01:21:12,868 --> 01:21:16,580
I will be the last person
you see from this world.

1026
01:21:16,663 --> 01:21:17,664
Right?

1027
01:21:18,749 --> 01:21:20,334
Shouldn't we stop him?

1028
01:21:20,417 --> 01:21:22,920
He said he won't die. Leave him.

1029
01:21:24,088 --> 01:21:26,173
Pull me up now, you asshole. Pull me up!

1030
01:21:28,258 --> 01:21:32,012
Babel E&C bought this building
through illegal means.

1031
01:21:33,180 --> 01:21:36,975
And I will not forgive their atrocity.

1032
01:21:37,768 --> 01:21:39,394
Unless you want to die, pull me up.

1033
01:21:39,478 --> 01:21:40,729
Now!

1034
01:21:42,064 --> 01:21:44,733
I'll get this building back
no matter what.

1035
01:21:45,776 --> 01:21:48,612
And I will make all of you
pay for what you did.

1036
01:21:51,281 --> 01:21:54,993
This building belongs to me.

1037
01:21:56,120 --> 01:21:58,122
That was Italian, right? What did he say?

1038
01:21:58,205 --> 01:21:59,581
-What?
-What did he say?

1039
01:21:59,665 --> 01:22:00,916
He said…

1040
01:22:03,961 --> 01:22:06,755
<i>È mio!</i>

1041
01:22:23,313 --> 01:22:25,274
SPECIAL THANKS TO JIN SUN-KYU,
LEE HEE-JUN, JEONG SOON-WON

1042
01:22:51,300 --> 01:22:53,135
<i>I don't expect you to believe me.</i>

1043
01:22:53,218 --> 01:22:54,052
<i>"Threatened"?</i>

1044
01:22:54,136 --> 01:22:55,596
Are you still pulling that stunt of yours?

1045
01:22:55,679 --> 01:22:59,308
I will blow both you and the tenants away
with this stunt.

1046
01:22:59,391 --> 01:23:01,643
<i>My experience tells me
that there's more to this.</i>

1047
01:23:01,727 --> 01:23:04,271
<i>A reason enough to make them act this way.</i>

1048
01:23:04,354 --> 01:23:06,815
<i>He could have secretly stashed
a fortune in Korea.</i>

1049
01:23:06,899 --> 01:23:09,860
<i>Aren't we the best in the country
when it comes to playing dirty?</i>

1050
01:23:09,943 --> 01:23:12,738
I don't like things dragging on,
so cut it short.

1051
01:23:12,821 --> 01:23:15,365
-Assholes like them should be made to pay.
-"Assholes"?

1052
01:23:15,449 --> 01:23:17,284
Cha-young! Tomorrow at 11 p.m.

1053
01:23:17,367 --> 01:23:20,496
<i>Legal or not, we'll get the job done.</i>

1054
01:23:21,205 --> 01:23:22,498
<i>We have to stop them no matter what.</i>

1055
01:23:22,581 --> 01:23:24,041
Hey!

1056
01:23:24,124 --> 01:23:26,168
<i>I thought I'd do the same as you did.</i>

1057
01:23:26,251 --> 01:23:28,170
